{
  "stem": "1684.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 14.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We were standing on the appellplatz till they took us out.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The next day, by-- it was by 1 o'clock until we got in there, it was in the evening, we didn't have anything to drink, not a drop of water-- and it's-- nothing to eat.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But anyhow, this wasn't the worst thing.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The worst thing was, that we saw my sister-in-law, who was with the kids.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She was walking by and she said, you see, I'm going to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They knew that this is the end.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I mean, she took the kids, and they-- and the little boys, they wanted want to go.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "My brother-in-law, at that time, he came into our group from Madritsch.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So he was safe.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But his boys wanted to get into our group.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They were 11 and 13 years old.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I don't remember exactly their ages.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But they wanted to come to our group, to Madritsch.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And Goeth chased them out.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And my husband will tell you, the third time, he said, I'm going to shoot you.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So they had to go with their mother to Auschwitz to be gassed.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So that's the last time I saw them.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Then we came to Plaszow, and we worked for Madritsch.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "We were very lucky-- my husband and me, we both got day shift, which meant we went into the magazine, where they were-- the ready-made clothes came in there.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And I had to make out all the office work, like the [NON-ENGLISH] it was called-- you know, how much goes out, and what kind of article it is, and things like that.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "So we had the day shift, which was very good.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And the lageralteste, the Jewish lageralteste, his sister worked with me, too.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Now, we worked there for-- for very many months.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
